{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1772556499,"nonce":"iKtEjiyLf+3Qp3BDBtI6srDZI+I=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOQ241x87vdlDazqdg6aU"},"target":"568225d1e21f88eac118527c5285f184f87a5f3e0db736f36893a28a747d9413","message":"## Context\n\nPart of #263 (Simplify scripts and Makefile interface). Emerged from brainstorming\nduring #325 (ADR-0007: Retain Make with dependency tracking).\n\nThe current Makefile has 19+ targets that grew organically. With the decision to adopt\nstamp-file dependencies (#332), the target surface area needs intentional design — not\njust adding stamps to existing targets, but rethinking what the user actually types and\nwhat should happen.\n\n## Agreed Design\n\n### Tier 1: Setup Chain (stamp-based, mostly invisible)\n\nThese are internal Make dependencies triggered automatically by `make build`:\n\n```\nbootstrap (system packages, ROS 2)\n    ↓\nsetup-dev (venv, pre-commit, hooks)\n    ↓\nmanifest (clone manifest repo, create symlinks)\n    ↓\nper-layer setup (vcs import, re-triggered by .repos file changes)\n    ↓\nbuild\n```\n\nKey decisions:\n- **Dev tools are non-optional** — `setup-dev` is early in the chain (before first\n  possible commit), not a separate opt-in step\n- **`setup-all` stays** as a convenience target (\"setup without building\")\n- **Per-layer targets removed** — `setup-core`, `setup-underlay`, `setup-platforms`,\n  `setup-sensors`, `setup-simulation`, `setup-ui` go away; the stamp chain handles them\n- **First-run prompt** — interactive manifest setup (location, layout explanation)\n  unless `CI=1` or `NONINTERACTIVE=1` env var is set (details in #330)\n\n### Tier 2: Developer Workflow (explicit targets)\n\nWhat the user actually types day-to-day:\n\n| Target | Purpose | Dependencies |\n|---|---|---|\n| `build` | Build everything (auto-setup if needed) | Tier 1 chain |\n| `test` | Test everything | `build` |\n| `lint` | All pre-commit hooks (subsumes `format`) | `setup-dev` |\n| `clean` | Remove build artifacts | None |\n| `dashboard` | Unified coordination view | None (read-only) |\n| `validate` | Pass/fail workspace check (CI-oriented) | None (read-only) |\n| `help` | Self-documenting target list | None |\n\n### Tier 3: Agent Orchestration \u0026 Maintenance (unchanged for now)\n\n| Target | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `agent-build` | Build sandboxed agent Docker image |\n| `agent-run` | Launch agent container for a worktree |\n| `agent-shell` | Launch agent container with bash (debug) |\n| `push-gateway` | Process pending push requests from containers |\n| `sync` | Safely sync all repositories |\n| `lock` / `unlock` | Workspace exclusive access |\n| `revert-feature` | Revert all commits for an issue |\n| `pr-triage` | Cross-repo PR triage |\n| `generate-skills` | Regenerate Claude Code slash commands |\n\nThese stay as-is for now. Future work (dispatch, agent-status, coordinator\npatterns) tracked separately.\n\n## What Changes\n\n| Current Target | Fate |\n|---|---|\n| `setup-core` | Removed — stamp chain |\n| `setup-underlay` | Removed — stamp chain |\n| `setup-platforms` | Removed — stamp chain |\n| `setup-sensors` | Removed — stamp chain |\n| `setup-simulation` | Removed — stamp chain |\n| `setup-ui` | Removed — stamp chain |\n| `setup-all` | Stays — convenience \"setup without build\" |\n| `format` | Removed — `lint` covers it |\n| `status` | Removed — merged into `dashboard` |\n| `status-quick` | Removed — `dashboard` with quick mode |\n| `health-check` | Removed — merged into `dashboard` or first-run flow |\n| `setup-dev` | Stays — but becomes stamp dependency, not user-facing |\n\n**Net result**: 19+ targets → ~14, with a cleaner mental model (3 tiers).\n\n## Dashboard Concept\n\nThe `dashboard` target replaces `status`, `status-quick`, and `health-check` as a\nunified coordination view:\n\n- Active worktrees + their issue + branch + dirty/clean status\n- PR status per worktree (open, review state, CI status)\n- Stale worktrees (no recent activity, already-merged PRs)\n- Issues ready for agent work that haven't been started\n- Quick mode via `make dashboard QUICK=1` (skip sync + GitHub API calls)\n\nThis serves human developers now and becomes a coordinator agent's reporting\nsurface later.\n\n## Multi-Agent Coordination (Future Direction)\n\nCurrent workflow: 3-4 terminals, each with an agent working a different issue through\nthe lifecycle (identify → review → plan → execute → review → merge). The human is the\nstate tracker and dispatcher.\n\nNear-term architecture to consider:\n- GitHub Issues as the task queue (labels like `agent-ready`, `agent-in-progress`)\n- Worktree scripts already enforce isolation per agent\n- Container mode (`agent-run`) as the execution boundary\n- Dashboard as the unified status surface\n- Coordinator agent pattern — one agent managing others\n\n## Related Issues\n\n- #263 — Simplify scripts and Makefile interface (parent)\n- #325 — ADR-0007: Retain Make with dependency tracking (decision)\n- #332 — Refactor Makefile with stamp-file dependencies (implementation)\n- #330 — Improve first-run initialization UX\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":5,"timestamp":1772554276,"nonce":"ceoA1qvrfvqlt96CSsQv21+7uWc=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87vdlDazwAAAAVovlcU"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]}]}